# Main Portal - DataFabric Academy

## Parent Rule Reference
This repository follows the **Global Academy-as-Code Policy** defined in `🚀 Academy Root/.cursorrules`. All rules from the parent apply unless explicitly overridden below.

## Repository Context
- **Repository**: `DataFabric-Academy/DataFabric-Academy.github.io`
- **Purpose**: Main portal hub connecting all course repositories
- **URL**: https://datafabric.academy
- **Base URL**: `/` (root)
- **Deployment**: GitHub Pages via GitHub Actions

## Portal-Specific Standards

### Content Structure
- **i18n Support**: Thai (default) and English locales
- **Blog**: Enabled - Use for announcements and cross-course content
- **Docs Route**: `/` (root path for main documentation)
- **Cross-References**: Link to course repositories using relative paths:
  - `/course-ms-sql/` for SQL Server course
  - `/course-power-bi/` for Power BI course
  - `/course-n8n/` for n8n course

### Technical Focus
- **Primary Role**: Navigation hub and academy overview
- **Content Type**: Meta-documentation, course catalog, academy policies
- **Integration**: Must maintain links to all course repositories

### Docusaurus Configuration
- **Config File**: `website/docusaurus.config.ts`
- **Sidebar**: `website/sidebars.ts`
- **i18n Structure**: See `website/i18n-STRUCTURE.md` for details

## AI Context Guidelines
- When referencing courses, always use the correct baseUrl paths
- Maintain consistency with course repository naming conventions
- Check cross-references to ensure all course links are valid
- Portal content should be language-agnostic (support both th/en)

